12/12/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Bulgaria opened its embassy in Podgorica on Monday (December 11th), to coincide with the 110th anniversary of the launch of bilateral diplomatic ties. Sofia plans to choose an ambassador by year's end.
In other news, the European Parliament approved in separate votes Tuesday the nominations of Bulgaria's Meglena Kuneva and Romania's Leonard Orban as EU Commissioners. Kuneva will be responsible for consumer protection, Orban for multilingualism. (Pobjeda, Vijesti, Dnevnik, Darik - 12/12/06) 
